content: @Cooper Thompson / @Brian Postlethwaite , @Eric Haas , @Lloyd McKenzie @Bryn Rhodes @Michelle (Moseman) Miller there are currently 40 or so breaking changes waiting to be applied to the spec across CDS, PA, PC, OO, and in the patterns stuff. What's the timeline for making these changes?
I'm going to be working on things this weekend, and hoping to have some assistance from @Cooper Thompson and @Andrew Torres over the next 2 weeks.
ok great. Please get the breaking changes done first
(Almost got our ballot reconciliation for the non Patient stuff done this morning, 6 left)
Will do.
thx
Working on them now, most of them applied, the question you just answered about the ig just cleared the way for the rest of them.
ok great
I'm going on vactation next week so it is going to be tight. I'm focused on Observation, DR, and SR, Specimen and Task, t I'll see what is left in the breakng change department.
Here is a summary of OO trackers marked as breaking or substantive:

• GF#16186 still need to add an example - substantive stuff applied
  • GF#16100 - GF#16098 are all for BDP to which I am not assigned.
  • GF#14450, GF#10300, GF#10299, GF#10297. GF#10297 - this is a general trackers for all the pattern stuff across all OO resources including the new drafty stuff I think I've applied everything to Observation, DR, SR, NO, still need to review Task, assigned DeviceRequest, DeviceStatement, SupplyRequest ,SupplyDelivery to Jose C-T.
There are a couple of susbstantive trackers for Specimen in the docket and I think that is all. Not tracking any of the draft stuff.
ok thank. Who is responsible for BDP?
and have a good vacation.
assuming Bob M. have not been keeping close tabs on them.
@ Bob Milius ?
I'll do mine on either Friday or Saturday.
I'll help Eric if there's anything still needed for OO

@Grahame Grieve I should be caught up on the Patient Care trackers to be applied. I wonder if you are referring to GF#15962, which is the tracker that I pinged you about earlier. It has a dependency on newly added LOINC codes, so I was waiting on you to upgrade LOINC on the terminology server.
ok try again - I've upgraded it to 2.64 a few hours ago
Will do!!

@Grahame Grieve My local build still fails saying it can't find the new LOINC codes in 2.64

[java] ERROR @ CareTeam.category.coding (line 0, col0): careteam-example:: CareTeam.category.coding: Error validating code "LA27976-2" in system "http://loinc.org": Error unmarshalling resource: Unable to find code LA27976-2 in http://loinc.org version 2.64 (src = InstanceValidator)
[java] ERROR @ CareTeam.category.coding: careteam-example:: CareTeam.category.coding: Error validating code "LA27976-2" in system "http://loinc.org": Error unmarshalling resource: Unable to find code LA27976-2 in http://loinc.org version 2.64 (src = InstanceValidator)

That said, I see the LOINC codes: https://s.details.loinc.org/LOINC/86744-0.html?sections=Comprehensive
Is there some gotcha with using LOINC answer codes?
Some of the LA codes that are available on the LOINC website aren't "official" yet - which means they don't show up in the FHIR terminology server
First Released in Version: 2.61 - so that's probably not it

FWIW, I have an email from Swapna Abhyankar back in April saying

In response to Michelle’s question about whether the codes have been approved - I have updated the answer list attached to LOINC 86744-0 in our database. 86744-0 was published in a previous release, and if you look it up right now you’ll see it with the old answer list. After our next release in June, you will see that code attached to the updated list.
The codes will be available in LOINC v2.65 (June 2018).
In sum, I question whether that "First Released in Version" is referring to the question -- and not the updated answers.
@Lloyd McKenzie If I pinged Swapna about these new codes, will he know what "official" means? If not, can you elaborate on what filters may exist in the terminology server?
That's more an @Grahame Grieve question...
clarification - the June 2018 LOINC release is 2.64 (which is available now)

@Rob Hausam FYI - the new LOINC codes aren't recognized by the terminology server, which was upgraded last night to 2.64 -- so I'm trying to find out whether the codes just aren't "official" yet. No clue what that means, hoping Grahame or you can help clarify!
hmm bug in my server somewhere - still chasing it

while I'm here:

  • 45 breaking changes to apply
  • 112 substantiative changes
  • 942(!) non-substantiative changes to apply
That's for everyone, not just you, correct?
yes everyone
infraustructure substantiative (breaking + non) are almost done
I can verify that code LA27976-2 is included in the LOINC 2.64 release AnswerList.csv file, and it is included in the LL4590-7 value set on fhir.loinc.org (the new official LOINC FHIR sever)
yes definitely a bug in my server. Not helped by LOINC continuing to change their distribution formats...

yes, true
but this format has some improvements - and hopefully it will be stable :)

issues open for me (e.g. waiting for committee input:

  • GF#13545: element definition / slicing (FHIR-I)
  • GF#15883: Questionnaire.item.definition & canonical(ElementDefinition) (FHIR-I)
  • GF#9047: defining code systems (Vocab + FHIR-I)
• GF#16143: ValueSet.status definitions (Vocab)
